        <description>&lt;img src="http://localhost:1313/post/images/npm-logo.png" alt="Featured image of post NPM Introduction" /&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;brief-description&#34;&gt;Brief Description
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;NPM, short for Node Package Manager, is a tool for managing and sharing JavaScript code packages. It is the default package manager for the Node.js platform, allowing developers to download and install various JavaScript packages and tools from the NPM repository. With NPM, developers can easily find, install, update, and remove dependencies, making the development and maintenance of JavaScript projects more efficient and convenient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to installing and managing packages, NPM also offers other features, such as publishing your own packages to the NPM repository, managing project dependencies, and running script commands. Developers can use NPM to build and manage their JavaScript projects and share their code with other developers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Overall, NPM is a powerful tool that provides convenient package management functions for the JavaScript community, facilitating collaboration and knowledge sharing among developers.&lt;/p&gt;
